  "prompt": "How do I increase font size in Quora?",
  "response": "To increase the font size on Quora, you can try the following methods:\n\n1. **Browser Zoom**: Most web browsers allow you to zoom in on a webpage, which will also increase the font size. You can usually do this by pressing `Ctrl` and `+` (Windows) or `Command` and `+` (Mac) to zoom in. To reset, use `Ctrl` and `0` (Windows) or `Command` and `0` (Mac).\n\n2. **Browser Settings**: You can change the default font size in your browser settings. For example, in Chrome, go to Settings > Appearance > Font size, and select a larger size.\n\n3. **Accessibility Features**: If you're using a device that has accessibility features, you can often increase text size through those settings. For instance, on Windows, you can go to Settings > Ease of Access > Display, and adjust the text size.\n\n4. **Custom CSS (for advanced users)**: If you're familiar with custom CSS, you can use a browser extension to inject CSS styles that increase font size on Quora specifically.\n\n5. **Mobile App Settings**: If you are using the Quora mobile app, you may need to adjust the font size in your device's accessibility settings, as the app itself may not have specific options for font size.\n\nKeep in mind that these changes will affect how you view Quora and possibly other websites as well.",
